    rating: "Pretty Good"
    comments: "Helps establish the tone"
  }
  sound {
    rating: "Good"
    comments: "Because there is no dialogue, the sound is very important in helping move the story forward"
  }
  animation {
    rating: "Great"
    comments: "Very beautiful and well done; a true technological acheivement that this was all done in Blender on a 4 million dollar budget as the animation rivals something you would see from Dreamwork's 'The Wild Robot'"
  }
  pacing: "Pacing is a bit slowed down because of the lack of dialogue, but the movie is already short"
  climax: "Climax is pretty well executed"
  tone: "Tone is similiar to other hero's journey movies, but in an adorable, animal way"
  final_notes: "This movie needs to be celebrated for being entirely animated through Blender and for having such a low budget"
  overall: "Overall, a technical achievement that needs to be celebrated as they created a visually beautiful movie that is entirely animated with Blender on a 4 million dollar budget, rivaling the work from big-budget studios like Dreamworks and Pixar"
